book.page:
[[{{w|3rd of Simmun Ut}}]]

Speculator Ptodelia reporting. The edge of the Moghra'yi is in view, and I shall not lament leaving the salt bluffs and cliffs behind. The rolling dunes look almost gentle in comparison, were it not for their unpleasant dwellers. Caravan leader Timuqq told me today the caravan will be making a detour, the saltback refusing to cross a part of the desert. They would not tell me why -- dromad trade secrets, I wager. I shall see about leaving the caravan before that, as I see little point in making my route longer than it needs to be. Speculator Ptodelia, out.


[[{{w|6th of Simmun Ut}}]]

{{emote|*Heavy wind makes most of the entry indecipherable.*}}


[[{{w|7th of Simmun Ut}}]]

Speculator Ptodelia reporting. I split from the caravan four days ago, but did not report on it. Yesterday, Qudish winds rose up eastward in the early morning. By High Salt Sun, a proper saltstorm was raging -- Academy be thanked, experimental tracheal filters are as useful east of the Moghra'yi as they are west. With vision compromised, I stayed close to the packbot and happened upon some sort of...

{{emote|*An old, masculine voice calls out in the distance, and the next words are uttered away from the recorder.*}}

No Warden, I am logging my travels for posterity... Yes, on my machine. I give you my word I will not include the location of this place. I shall leave a copy, if that eases your mind.

... some hut by an old boneyard. In accordance with the Principles I shall document it, but the old warden bids me to keep its location secret. In quite a fascinating way, the eastern saltbacks seem to naturally gravitate toward this place in their old age. Unlike what I previously observed in the salt bluffs...

{{emote|*The rest of the entry is a thesis on compared saltback cultural traditions, concluded by the usual "Speculator Ptodelia, out".*}}
